\subsection{${\mathfrak{{m}}}$-Exactness, ${\mathfrak{{m}}}$-Saturation}
\begin{Def}\label{Def:mEx}
Let ${\mathfrak{{m}}}$ is an infinite cardinal.

A {lim-rim}\ $E$ over an (infinite) set $B$ is called {{\em\bf} ${\mathfrak{{m}}}$-exact} if it is separated and exactness of the diagram of the natural mapping, as in Definition \ref{Def:ex}, holds for the inclusion $I\to I\cup\{i\}$ for any $|I|<{\mathfrak{{m}}}$.

