The ``weak'' (equivalence) relation $\cap_n{^\star}{^\star} U_n)$, in our case saying that the difference being less than any $\nu(\nu(a))$,\,\,$a>0,a\in{\mathbb{{R}}}$. Lets call such ${^\star}{^\star}$reals {\em ``weakly infinitesimal''}. These are the elements equivalent to $0$, and they include all ${^\star}\nu$ of infinitesimals. In fact, any ${^\star}{^\star} a\in{^\star}{^\star}{\mathbb{{R}}}$ with standard bounds is thus ``weakly'' equivalent to $\nu(\nu\big(\textrm{st}({^\star}\textrm{st}({^\star}{^\star} a))\big))$, which is the only standard element in its equivalence class.{\par\medskip}

